               CHECKLIST
Do’s
•	Think before posting – Make sure your content is respectful and appropriate. 
•	Maintain privacy settings – Keep your personal information secure. 
•	Be professional – Remember that recruiters and professors may view your profile. 
•	Verify information before sharing – Avoid spreading fake news or misinformation. 
•	Respect others online – Be polite and considerate in comments and messages. 
 Don’ts
•	Don’t share personal/confidential information – Avoid posting phone numbers, addresses, or sensitive data. 
•	Don’t engage in cyberbullying or trolling – Harmful behavior can have serious consequences. 
•	Don’t post inappropriate or offensive content – It can damage your reputation. 
•	Don’t overshare – Too much personal information can be risky. 
•	Don’t believe everything online blindly – Always cross-check facts before trusting content
